<title>TURKEY: Turkey's sugar workers get about 65-pct pay rises.</title>
<headline>Turkey's sugar workers get about 65-pct pay rises.</headline>
<dateline>ANKARA 1997-03-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Turkey's 32,000 state sugar workers received pay rises of about 65 percent for this year after collective bargaining talks with state-run sugar refineries employer Turkseker, union officials said.</p>
<p>They said the workers would get a one-off 15-percent bonus on top of increased salaries, whose average will rise to 53 million lira net from 32 million lira per month.</p>
<p>Turkseker operates 25 of the 28 sugar refineries in Turkey, which had an annual inflation of about 85 percent in January.</p>
<p>--Ankara Newsroom, 90-312-4462940</p>
